          <title type="preferred">Rāmacāpastava</title>
          <title type="variant">Cāpastava</title>
          <editor key="p_4" role="aut">Rāmabhadra Dīkṣita</editor>
          <note type="genre">Hymn</note>
          <note type="subject">Vaiṣṇava</note>
          <note type="bibliographical">Stavamaṇimālā, Sarasvatī Vilāsa Series 6</note>
          <note type="bibliographical">Kāvyamālā Gucchaka 12</note>
          <note type="bibliographical">NCC vol. 24, 128 and 188</note>
          <note type="bibliographical">Adyar vol. 4, part 1, ms. 1859, 310–311</note>
          <note type="bibliographical">Adyar vol. 1, 193a</note>
          <note type="general">One of the 9 hymns that are printed in the Stavamaṇimālā as Sarasvatī Vilāsa Series 6 (ed. Subrahmanya Sastri)</note>
          <note type="general">See Thiruvengadathan pg. 17 and Raghavan introduction to Śāhendravilāsa pg. 41</note>
          <note type="general">Rāma's bow is eulogised here in 112 verses, in Śārdūlavikrīḍita metre. Rāma is characterised as a hero who brings welfare to the universe (see Sinhā pg. 306)</note>
